Node.Notes: Uncertain, apparently participle of a verb that means "be wise/prudent." Could mean psalm meant to instruct or skill with which psalm was composed or even indicate meditation. Used also in titles of ps42; 44; 45; 52; 55; 74; 78; 88; 89; and 143. Also in ps47:7 and 2c30:22.
Exact figure uncertain, but sense is probably that the psalmist's strength/vitality is dried up by the summer heat.
Uncertain. Apparently "moisture," some posit word could mean "vitality/strength." Many change word to "tongue."
Uncertain. Many change to "time of stress." If time of finding, perhaps a time when God may be found.
Text uncertain, see commentaries, read here as passive.
Figure of a devastating flood for dangers and troubles.
Without understanding may modify both horse and mule and not just mule.
Unknown, with many different suggestions. Perhaps an ornamental restraint.. Many just skip it and translate the general sense of something like "who must be controlled by bit and bridle."
